ards. Given ongoing uncertainty surrounding cross-border transfer mechanisms, this approach may create potential vulnerability.\n\n## Aggregate Summary\nOut of the five contracts reviewed, three present elevated or critical concerns requiring legal attention. The most common issues include indefinite retention periods, insufficient safeguards for international data transfers, and automated decision-making without human oversight. One contract (contract_003.txt) demonstrates best practices and poses minimal concern.\n\n## Recommendations\n1. Implement defined data retention limits across all agreements.\n2. Establish appropriate safeguards for international data transfers, such as Standard Contractual Clauses.\n3. Introduce human oversight for profiling and automated decision-making activities.\n4. Remove or revise clauses referencing monetary consequences under data protection law where possible.\nEOF"}
